The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is probably aimed at provoking such a dispute, says the Research Institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure on the part of the political leaders: "Persons of public life have left the discussion of the Roma question to representatives of radical political groups who have now built their political strategy on the Roma-Hungary contradiction".
It is believed that this would aggravate the problem, make reasonable dialogue impossible, promote extremities and increase the likelihood of violent conflicts.
The research institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guard, not least thanks to the enormous attention of the domestic and foreign media, "had significantly damaged the image of Hungary abroad, especially in terms of confidence in stability and democratic maturity".
We remember: since autumn 2006 the reorganisation of radical and extreme right-wing groups in Hungary has been constantly on the rise, so that since summer 2007 several organizations called "national self-defense association" have been founded.
"These groups are commonplace that they define themselves as civil organizations, while openly boasting of preparing their members for - sometimes armed - defence tasks (catastrophe protection, national defence, order-keeping), calling on the improbability of the police, the army, the army of the state itself," it said.
And then again: all of this is done in accordance with the method of trying to disguise different political and party-drugs based on the political and party-drugs of the population as a bourgeois initiative.
The emphasis on the civil character and form of the union is not merely to avoid legal obstacles that might arise in the course of the registration to court - it is at the same time a political strategy.
As the analysis shows, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are also a risk-enhancing factor for relations with neighbouring countries.
"In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been cited as a potential source of danger in several neighbouring countries, according to some ultra-nationalist politicians of certain neighbouring countries, in the emergence of the Hungarian Guard, the confirmation of its own anti-Hungary policy.
All of this has an impact on the political stability of the region" - it was said.
