The Congress agrees with the MIFID Directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with the parliamentary drafting which ended its meeting today with the Senate Congress decision on the additional/amendments to the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of allowing the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of Congress and Senate delegates who in their negotiations and votes had pursued the aim of establishing the best possible regulation ensuring the security of investors and regulating individual business activities in order to ensure a generally efficient market activity.
In addition to modernising the financial markets, MIFID, which redefines the securities service regulation, pursues an improvement in investor protection, an increase in the control entitlement of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and the promotion of cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive allows specialised companies as well as natural or legal persons to provide financial advice and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), the consulting companies that are associated with investment firms and investment firms of securities.
It also extends the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions so that the regulated circulation markets are added to the multilateral systems of securities business and the systems for the internationalisation of trading contracts, which would ultimately compete with the current economic operators.
The law requires investment firms to report the focus of their business profile, confrontation and the forms of dealing with risks on the market and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV's control task.
The Congress Economic Commission subsequently provided for further changes, with the decision that the titled debt securities must now be considered as complex financial resources for the investor due to their high level of risk, as a result of the US mortgage and banking crisis. (US mortgage crisis)
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal limitation of the fields of work of qualified economists was used; 30 years after 1977, the regulation was adopted which restricted the fields of work reserved for economists.
The Senate, for its part, set out new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator who works on foreign account, does not require authorisation by CNMV and can offer its services for commercialization of products and for customer acquisition to several investment companies at the same time.
The harmonised consumer price index (CPI) rose by five tenths in November and is now 4.1%.
The indicator used by Eurostat to assess the inflation rate within the European Union provides the average price trend in Spain in November.
Its publication is in line with the principles of Eurostat and the European Central Bank (ECB), which seek to compare the location and quality of US products by publishing the data.
The forecast for the indicator can be prepared in advance by using the same approach as the harmonised consumer price index, but at the same time using several other statistical modelling methods to estimate the information that does not exist at the time of the calculation.
However, the Spanish Statistical Office (INE) recommended that the pre-determined indicator should only serve as a benchmark and therefore not be in line with the final result announced on 14 December.
The consumer price index (CPI) will continue to remain at a relatively high level
According to the Deputy Head of Government and the Minister for Economic and Financial Affairs Pedro Solbes, the increase in the CPI in November was a temporary development and at the same time ensured that the price index would remain at a relatively high level in the coming months.
Nevertheless , in the halls of the Congress building , Solbes noted that even if the current number is not good , the inflation gap between Spain and the other members of the Monetary Union has remained more or less the same in recent years .
Moreover, he explained that there were fewer surprises in November than in the previous month, in which the government did not expect such a high increase.
We expected a value of around 4% , the Minister of Economics and Finance announced in view of the forecast published today .
