Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance, which covers a possible case of damage caused by the driver, includes a high cost burden, the amount of which is again dependent on various factors, including age, gender, date of the creation of the driving licence, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right vehicle insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance company.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract that determines that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is in return obliged to present the corresponding amount of compensation in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance composed of several factors, including age, gender, date of production of the driving licence, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance undertakings shall determine their prices according to the statistics so that higher contributions are due in the event of a higher risk of accident.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women need to make fewer contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since, according to the statistical values and thus also according to the companies, these tend to be less accidents than single persons.
The benefits attached to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus the probability of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In setting up the premium, insurance must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver also needs to study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
We are now listing the most important points that should be considered when choosing insurance, in order not only to make a performance choice but also to make a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds face numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and the young driver's license.
Even if it would be best for the ideal insurance protection to take out a full insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The careful drivers can choose a full-scale cashier with self-interest, so that the benefits of a full-scale insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This kind of contract involves that the customer must pay part of the amount caused by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the sum to be paid , says Luis Noguera, Spain's prime representative at First Europa, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is the extended insurance, which assures customers against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused by their own car.
Furthermore, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's a advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is in your hand to reduce insurance costs; your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty includes an increase in the said tariff.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on society and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it may allow itself to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year-old mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that increasing driving practice reduces the accident rate.
It is therefore most useful to opt for a full insurance insurance with self-interest.
Usually, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish leader of the European company, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second practical year after the beginner's fear has been removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out full cash insurance; of course only if it allows the financial situation of the person concerned.
The insurers consider married couples with children to be customers with the lowest accident rate, and consequently their contribution payments are low.
In this case, full cash insurance with a self participation (with an amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which will only be used for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution, says Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is appropriate to take out a full insurance with a self-employed contribution (with an amount of EUR 150) or an extended insurance which only applies to a sufficiently high credit.
Finally, you have to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it entails high costs that require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
